        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Some remarks about the doc if that’s ok here:</p>
<ol>
<li>For consistency with the structure, the text</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p>The procedure of installing <code>firefox-esr</code> is now complete.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>may be replaced with a description of what the command that follows,</p>
<blockquote>
<p>sudo --set-home -u clearnet bash</p>
</blockquote>
<p>actually does.</p>
<ol start="2">
<li>Instructions to remove the browser when done with it required in this case?</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p>apt-get remove firefox-esr</p>
</blockquote>
<p>or</p>
<blockquote>
<p>apt-get purge firefox-esr</p>
</blockquote>
<p>and remove user and directory?</p>
<p>Or not bother with it since this is clearly a specially configured Gateway only used when really necessary?</p>
